<div>
<h2>Welcome to Z-Billing for Salesforce.com!</h2>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Thank you for installing Z-Billing for Salesforce.com! Before you get started, there are a couple steps you have to complete to get the most out of this application. (Be sure to perform the following steps as
a System Administrator of Salesforce.com.)</p>
</div>

<!-- task -->
<div>
<div class="bPageBlock secondaryPalette">
<div class="pbHeader">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
   <tbody>
      <tr>
         <td class="pbTitle">
         <h2>Step 1: Configure your Account Layouts</h2>
         </td>
         <td class="pbHelp"></td>
      </tr>
   </tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class="pbBody">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" class="setupOverview">
   <tbody>
      <tr>
         <td>Follow the below steps to configure your Account Layouts:
         <ol>
            <li>Navigate to "Setup->App Setup->Customize->Accounts->Page Layouts".</li>
            <li>Click on the Account Layout you want the Z-Billing objects to appear on.</li>
            <li>Click on the "edit" link next to the Account Layout you want the Z-Billing objects to appear on.</li>
            <li>On the bottom-right hand of the page, there is a "View" drop-down. Select "Account Related Lists".</li>
            <li>In the "Account Related Lists" section, drag-and-drop the "Billing Accounts" item into the "Related List Section" of the Account Layout.</li>
            <li>Perform the same drag-and-drop for Subscriptions, Subscription Products and Subscription Charges.</li>
            <li>Click the "Save" button.</li>
         </ol>
         &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Additionally, you can customize which Z-Billing Object fields appear on the Account Related Lists. Below are
         the steps for customizing Subscription fields in the related list on the Account Layout.
         <ol>
            <li>From the Account "Edit Page Layout" page, click on the "Subscription" Related List section.</li>
            <li>Click on "Edit Properties". A window will pop up.</li>
            <li>In the Available Fields section, click on the MRR field.</li>
            <li>Click "Add" to add the field to the related list layout.
            <li>Repeat steps 3 and 4 for each field you wish to add to the view.</li>
            <li>It is recommended that you uncheck the box in the "Standard Buttons" section at the bottom of the pop-up (the one labeled "New [New]").  This will prevent users from attempting to enter new data.  Any new data entered in this way will be overwritten when the data is synchronized.</li> 
            <li>Click "OK" to close the pop up window.</li>
            <li>You may also add fields for Subscriptions and Subscription Product & Charges by repeating Steps 1 â€“ 5 for each of the objects.</li>
            <li>On the Account "Edit Page Layout" page, click the "Save" button.</li>
         </ol>
         &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; After completing the above steps, you should now see related lists in your Account Detail page.
         </td> 
      </tr>
   </tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class="pbFooter secondaryPalette">
