<div>
<p>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 
After associating a Zuora Customer Account with a Salesforce.com Account (Using a 15-character Salesforce.com Account ID 
in a Zuora Customer Account CRM Account ID), you can sync from Zuora and view Z-Billing information in Salesforce.com.
</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Finally, here are a few notes about this release:
<ol>
   <li>Billing Accounts, Subscriptions, Subscription Rate Plans and Subscription Charges should never be 
   edited in Salesforce.com. They should be edited in Zuora directly.</li>
   <li>Do not create any child objects of the above Z-Billing objects, as they are subject to deletion
   upon a re-sync.
</ol>
</p>
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Thanks again for using Z-Billing for Salesforce.com!
</p>

